<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-129-798  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 129 798.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  Feb 1989 v45 n2p133(17).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Connected component labeling of binary images on a mesh connectedmassively parallel processor. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Manohar, M.; Ramapriyan, H.K.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An algorithm is presented that consists three major steps forconnected component labeling of binary patterns using SIMD meshconnected computers.andP;  The three steps involve designating exactlyone seed point within each region, uniquely labeling each seedpoint, and expanding the labels to fill each pixel in therespective regions.andP;  Seed points may be identified by means of ashrinking algorithm or by the iterative replacement of each labelwith local minima or maxima.andP;  A consecutive set of numbers isassigned as labels to the seed points and parallel expansion tothe boundaries of the original pattern completes the connectedcomponent labeling.andP;  Computational complexities of the algorithmare discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Binary Number SystemAlgorithmsParallel ProcessingComputer GraphicsImage Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>